description:
&lt;p&gt;i-HEART Barnsley is a service run by Barnsley Healthcare Federation providing NHS care for the people of Barnsley. I-HEART is committed to providing a high level of care to our service users with over 95% of our patients who have used the service rating it as Excellent/Very Good.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main purpose of the Admin Support role is to deliver an effective and competent level of receptionist and clerical support and consistently deliver a ‘client-focused’ service which promotes good customer service and effective working relationships. You will be responsible for handling telephone enquires, booking and checking in patient appointments, preparing rooms for clinicians, locking premises, and supporting the smooth running of clinics with all other administrative tasks related to service provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be a team player with a good standard of education.  You will be self-motivated and possess excellent verbal and written communication skills. You will have the ability to use your own initiative to deal with problems and situation under pressure.     &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in administration/reception work is essential, ideally in a healthcare environment and a working knowledge of SystmOne/Lorenzo is highly desirable.  The position is to work on a rolling 2 week rota pattern which covers evenings and weekends as well as core office hours. The rota pattern involves working every other weekend. You will also need to be flexible in your hours to cover for holidays as and when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Proposed rota pattern:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 1: Tuesday, Thursday and Friday 4pm - 10.30pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Week 2: Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday 4pm - 10.30pm &lt;/p&gt;
